11/10/2009
ZURICH, Switzerland -- Armenian Foreign Minister Edward Nalbandian and his Turkish counterpart Ahmet Davutoglu signed in Zurich on Saturday (October 10th) two historical protocols to open the border between their countries and establish diplomatic ties. The signing ceremony took place at Zurich University in the presence of Swiss Foreign Minister Micheline Calmy-Rey, US Secretary of State Hillary Clinton, French Foreign Minister Bernard Kouchner and Russia's top diplomat Sergey Lavrov. EU foreign policy chief Javier Solana was also there. (AFP, Reuters, Anadolu news agency, AP, Aysor - 10/10/09)
